response: Ever since I was a child math has been difficult for me. I used to say that I hate math and that I am not good at it, but my mom told me to think positive. I still do not like it but I am not as bad as I thought. It just does not come easy for me and I really have to work at it. I always get extra help or go to tutoring or office hours. I have had a math tutor since the 5th grade but I found it to be helpful. It takes me a while to understand something so I tend to watch videos or do extra practice tests. I am a visual learner and I like when things are drawn out for me step by step, not just jumping to the answer and I don't know how I got there. I liked geometry but everything else like pre-calc and algebra were not my favorite.
